[CENTER][IMG]https://pvpindex.com/og-default.png[/IMG]

[SIZE=6][B]PvPIndex Battles[/B][/SIZE]
[SIZE=4]Verified ELO Tracking for Competitive PvP[/SIZE][/CENTER]

[B]PvPIndex Battles[/B] connects your Paper or Velocity server to [URL='https://pvpindex.com']pvpindex.com[/URL] — an open, tamper-proof ELO ranking platform for competitive Minecraft PvP. Every duel gets recorded, cryptographically signed, and submitted to the API; your players earn verified ratings they can compare against the rest of the network.

[HR][/HR]

[SIZE=5][B]Features[/B][/SIZE]

[LIST]
[*][B]10 built-in game modes[/B] — Sword, Pot, NoDebuff, Soup, Axe, Mace, Boxing, Sumo, Crystal, UHC
[*][B]Matchmaking queue[/B] with a fully configurable 54-slot GUI ([ICODE]gui.yml[/ICODE]), per-mode ELO, countdowns, and arena teleportation
[*][B]Cross-server challenges[/B] — [ICODE]/battle challenge <player> [mode][/ICODE] works standalone or routes through a connected Velocity proxy
[*][B]Network-wide tab completion[/B] — Velocity broadcasts all online players so [ICODE]/battle challenge <TAB>[/ICODE] shows names from every backend server
[*][B]Replay system[/B] — frame-by-frame battle recording with in-game [ICODE]/pvpmod replay <id>[/ICODE] playback
[*][B]Arena pool[/B] — procedural, schematic, and world-copy generation strategies; four bundled schematics included
[*][B]Moderation suite[/B] — reports, local bans, federated network-wide bans, real-time spectating
[*][B]PlaceholderAPI support[/B] — ELO, rank, win/loss, battle state, and battle type placeholders
[*][B]Fully configurable messages[/B] via [ICODE]messages.yml[/ICODE]
[*][B]HMAC-signed payloads[/B] — battles are cryptographically signed before transmission so the server cannot fake results
[*][B]Open ELO formula[/B] — K=32, trust-weighted implementation published under MIT at [URL='https://github.com/PVP-Index/battle-validator']github.com/PVP-Index/battle-validator[/URL]
[/LIST]

[HR][/HR]

